42//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
43std::string ExtensibleWave_ChannelMask (int32u ChannelMask)
44{
45 std::string Text;
46 if ((ChannelMask&0x0007)!=0x0000)
47 Text+="Front:";
48 if (ChannelMask&0x0001)
49 Text+=" L";
50 if (ChannelMask&0x0004)
51 Text+=" C";
52 if (ChannelMask&0x0002)
53 Text+=" R";
54
55 if ((ChannelMask&0x0600)!=0x0000)
56 Text+=", Side:";
57 if (ChannelMask&0x0200)
58 Text+=" L";
59 if (ChannelMask&0x0400)
60 Text+=" R";
61
62 if ((ChannelMask&0x0130)!=0x0000)
63 Text+=", Back:";
64 if (ChannelMask&0x0010)
65 Text+=" L";
66 if (ChannelMask&0x0100)
67 Text+=" C";
68 if (ChannelMask&0x0020)
69 Text+=" R";
70
71 if ((ChannelMask&0x0008)!=0x0000)
72 Text+=", LFE";
73
74 return Text;
75}
76
77//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
78std::string ExtensibleWave_ChannelMask2 (int32u ChannelMask)
79{
80 std::string Text;
81 int8u Count=0;
82 if (ChannelMask&0x0001)
83 Count++;
84 if (ChannelMask&0x0004)
85 Count++;
86 if (ChannelMask&0x0002)
87 Count++;
88 Text+=Ztring::ToZtring(Count).To_UTF8();
89 Count=0;
90
91 if (ChannelMask&0x0200)
92 Count++;
93 if (ChannelMask&0x0400)
94 Count++;
95 Text+="/"+Ztring::ToZtring(Count).To_UTF8();
96 Count=0;
97
98 if (ChannelMask&0x0010)
99 Count++;
100 if (ChannelMask&0x0100)
101 Count++;
102 if (ChannelMask&0x0020)
103 Count++;
104 Text+="/"+Ztring::ToZtring(Count).To_UTF8();
105 Count=0;
106
107 if (ChannelMask&0x0008)
108 Text+=".1";
109
110 return Text;
111}
112
113}

412{

414 Element_Size-=Alignement_ExtraByte;
415
416 DATA_BEGIN
417 LIST(AIFC)
418 ATOM_BEGIN

505 LIST(AVIX_movi_rec_)

509 ATOM_END

511 LIST(CDDA)

513 ATOM(CDDA_fmt_)

568 LIST(WAVE_data)
569 break;
570 ATOM(WAVE_cue_)
571 ATOM(WAVE_ds64)
572 ATOM(WAVE_fact)
573 ATOM(WAVE_fmt_)
574 ATOM(WAVE_ID3_)
575 ATOM(WAVE_id3_)
576 LIST(WAVE_INFO)
577 ATOM_DEFAULT_ALONE(WAVE_INFO_xxxx)
578 ATOM(WAVE_iXML)
579 ATOM_END
580 LIST(wave)
581 ATOM_BEGIN
582 LIST(wave_data)
583 break;
584 ATOM(wave_fmt_)
585 ATOM_END
586 DATA_END
587
588 if (Alignement_ExtraByte)
589 {
590 Element_Size+=Alignement_ExtraByte;
591 if (Element_Offset+Alignement_ExtraByte==Element_Size)
592 Skip_XX(Alignement_ExtraByte, "Alignement");
593 }
594}

663//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
664void File_Riff::AIFF_COMM()
665{
666 Element_Name("Common");
667
668 int32u numSampleFrames;
669 int16u numChannels, sampleSize;
670 float80 sampleRate;
671 //Parsing
672 Get_B2 (numChannels, "numChannels");
673 Get_B4 (numSampleFrames, "numSampleFrames");
674 Get_B2 (sampleSize, "sampleSize");
675 Get_BF10(sampleRate, "sampleRate");
676 if (Data_Remain()) //AIFC
677 {
678 int32u compressionType;
679 Get_C4 (compressionType, "compressionType");
680 Skip_PA( "compressionName");
681
682 //Filling
683 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_CC4(compressionType), Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Mpeg4);
684 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, Ztring().From_CC4(compressionType));
685 }
686 else
687 {
688 //Filling
689 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Format, "PCM");
690 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, "PCM");
691 }
692
693 //Filling
694 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_, numChannels);
695 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitDepth, sampleSize);
696 if (sampleRate)
697 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Duration, numSampleFrames/sampleRate*1000);
698 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_SamplingRate, sampleRate, 0);
699
700 //Compute the current codec ID
701 Element_Code=(int64u)-1;
702 Stream_ID=(int32u)-1;
703 stream_Count=1;
704
705 //Specific cases
706 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_SMPTEST0337_YES)
707 if (Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_CodecID).empty() && numChannels==2 && sampleSize<=32 && sampleRate==48000) //Some SMPTE ST 337 streams are hidden in PCM stream
708 {
709 File_SmpteSt0337* Parser=new File_SmpteSt0337;
710 Parser->Endianness='B';
711 Parser->Container_Bits=(int8u)sampleSize;
712 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
713 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
714 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get())
715 {
716 Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
717 Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
718 Demux_Level=4; //Intermediate
719 }
720 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
721 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
722 }
723 #endif
724
725 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PCM_YES)
726 File_Pcm* Parser=new File_Pcm;
727 Parser->Codec=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_CodecID);
728 if (Parser->Codec.empty() || Parser->Codec==__T("NONE"))
729 Parser->Endianness='B';
730 Parser->BitDepth=(int8u)sampleSize;
731 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
732 if (Demux_Rate)
733 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid = float64_int64s(Demux_Rate);
734 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get())
735 {
736 Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
737 Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
738 Demux_Level=4; //Intermediate
739 }
740 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
741 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid=(int64u)-1; //Disabling it, waiting for SMPTE ST 337 parser reject
742 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
743 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
744 Stream[Stream_ID].IsPcm=true;
745 Stream[Stream_ID].StreamKind=Stream_Audio;
746 #endif
747 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
748 BlockAlign=numChannels*sampleSize/8;
749 AvgBytesPerSec=(int32u)float64_int64s(BlockAlign*(float64)sampleRate);
750 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
751
752 Element_Code=(int64u)-1;
753 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
754 Open_Buffer_Init(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]);
755}

757//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
758void File_Riff::AIFF_COMT()
759{
760 //Parsing
761 int16u numComments;
762 Get_B2(numComments, "numComments");
763 for (int16u Pos=0; Pos<=numComments; Pos++)
764 {
765 Ztring text;
766 int16u count;
767 Element_Begin1("Comment");
768 Skip_B4( "timeStamp");
769 Skip_B4( "marker");
770 Get_B2 (count, "count");
771 count+=count%1; //always even
772 Get_Local(count, text, "text");
773 Element_End0();
774
775 //Filling
776 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Comment, text);
777 }
778}

1032//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1033void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_indx()
1034{
1035 Element_Name("Index");
1036
1037 int32u Entry_Count, ChunkId;
1038 int16u LongsPerEntry;
1039 int8u IndexType, IndexSubType;
1040 Get_L2 (LongsPerEntry, "LongsPerEntry"); //Size of each entry in aIndex array
1041 Get_L1 (IndexSubType, "IndexSubType");
1042 Get_L1 (IndexType, "IndexType");
1043 Get_L4 (Entry_Count, "EntriesInUse"); //Index of first unused member in aIndex array
1044 Get_C4 (ChunkId, "ChunkId"); //FCC of what is indexed
1045
1046 //Depends of size of structure...
1047 switch (IndexType)
1048 {
1049 case 0x01 : //AVI_INDEX_OF_CHUNKS
1050 switch (IndexSubType)
1051 {
1052 case 0x00 : AVI__hdlr_strl_indx_StandardIndex(Entry_Count, ChunkId); break;
1053 case 0x01 : AVI__hdlr_strl_indx_FieldIndex(Entry_Count, ChunkId); break; //AVI_INDEX_2FIELD
1054 default: Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
1055 }
1056 break;
1057 case 0x0 : //AVI_INDEX_OF_INDEXES
1058 switch (IndexSubType)
1059 {
1060 case 0x00 :
1061 case 0x01 : AVI__hdlr_strl_indx_SuperIndex(Entry_Count, ChunkId); break; //AVI_INDEX_2FIELD
1062 default: Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
1063 }
1064 break;
1065 default: Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
1066 }
1067}
1068
1069//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1070void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_indx_StandardIndex(int32u Entry_Count, int32u ChunkId)
1071{
1072 Element_Name("Standard Index");
1073
1074 //Parsing
1075 int64u BaseOffset, StreamSize=0;
1076 Get_L8 (BaseOffset, "BaseOffset");
1077 Skip_L4( "Reserved3");
1078 for (int32u Pos=0; Pos<Entry_Count; Pos++)
1079 {
1080 //Is too slow
1081 /*
1082 Element_Begin1("Index");
1083 int32u Offset, Size;
1084 Get_L4 (Offset, "Offset"); //BaseOffset + this is absolute file offset
1085 Get_L4 (Size, "Size"); //Bit 31 is set if this is NOT a keyframe
1086 Element_Info1(Size&0x7FFFFFFF);
1087 if (Size)
1088 Element_Info1("KeyFrame");
1089 Element_End0();
1090 */
1091
1092 //Faster method
1093 if (Element_Offset+8>Element_Size)
1094 break; //Malformed index
1095 int32u Offset=LittleEndian2int32u(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+(size_t)Element_Offset );
1096 int32u Size =LittleEndian2int32u(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+(size_t)Element_Offset+4)&0x7FFFFFFF;
1097 Element_Offset+=8;
1098
1099 //Stream Position and size
1100 if (Pos<300 || MediaInfoLib::Config.ParseSpeed_Get()==1.00)
1101 {
1102 Stream_Structure[BaseOffset+Offset-8].Name=ChunkId&0xFFFF0000;
1103 Stream_Structure[BaseOffset+Offset-8].Size=Size;
1104 }
1105 StreamSize+=(Size&0x7FFFFFFF);
1106 Stream[ChunkId&0xFFFF0000].PacketCount++;
1107
1108 //Interleaved
1109 if (Pos== 0 && (ChunkId&0xFFFF0000)==0x30300000 && Interleaved0_1 ==0)
1110 Interleaved0_1 =BaseOffset+Offset-8;
1111 if (Pos==Entry_Count/10 && (ChunkId&0xFFFF0000)==0x30300000 && Interleaved0_10==0)
1112 Interleaved0_10=BaseOffset+Offset-8;
1113 if (Pos== 0 && (ChunkId&0xFFFF0000)==0x30310000 && Interleaved1_1 ==0)
1114 Interleaved1_1 =BaseOffset+Offset-8;
1115 if (Pos==Entry_Count/10 && (ChunkId&0xFFFF0000)==0x30310000 && Interleaved1_10==0)
1116 Interleaved1_10=BaseOffset+Offset-8;
1117 }
1118 Stream[ChunkId&0xFFFF0000].StreamSize+=StreamSize;
1119 if (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
1120 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Garbage");
1121}

1125{
1126 Element_Name("Field Index");

1203//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1204void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds()
1205{
1206 Element_Info1("Audio");
1207
1208 //Parsing
1209 #if !MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1210 int32u AvgBytesPerSec;
1211 #endif //!MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1212 int16u FormatTag, Channels;
1213 BitsPerSample=0;
1214 Get_L2 (FormatTag, "FormatTag");
1215 Get_L2 (Channels, "Channels");
1216 Get_L4 (SamplesPerSec, "SamplesPerSec");
1217 Get_L4 (AvgBytesPerSec, "AvgBytesPerSec");
1218 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1219 Get_L2 (BlockAlign, "BlockAlign");
1220 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1221 Skip_L2( "BlockAlign");
1222 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1223 if (Element_Offset+2<=Element_Size)
1224 Get_L2 (BitsPerSample, "BitsPerSample");
1225
1226 if (FormatTag==1) //Only for PCM
1227 {
1228 //Coherancy
1229 if (BitsPerSample && SamplesPerSec*BitsPerSample*Channels/8==AvgBytesPerSec*8)
1230 AvgBytesPerSec*=8; //Found in one file. TODO: Provide information to end user about such error
1231
1232 //Computing of missing value
1233 if (!BitsPerSample && AvgBytesPerSec && SamplesPerSec && Channels)
1234 BitsPerSample=(int16u)(AvgBytesPerSec*8/SamplesPerSec/Channels);
1235 }
1236
1237 //Filling
1238 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Audio);
1239 Stream[Stream_ID].Compression=FormatTag;
1240 Ztring Codec; Codec.From_Number(FormatTag, 16);
1241 Codec.MakeUpperCase();
1242 CodecID_Fill(Codec, Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
1243 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, Codec); //May be replaced by codec parser
1244 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec_CC, Codec);
1245 if (Channels)
1246 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Channel_s_, (Channels!=5 || FormatTag==0xFFFE)?Channels:6);
1247 if (SamplesPerSec)
1248 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_SamplingRate, SamplesPerSec);
1249 if (AvgBytesPerSec)
1250 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitRate, AvgBytesPerSec*8);
1251 if (BitsPerSample)
1252 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitDepth, BitsPerSample);
1253 Stream[Stream_ID].AvgBytesPerSec=AvgBytesPerSec; //Saving bitrate for each stream
1254 if (SamplesPerSec && TimeReference!=(int64u)-1)
1255 {
1256 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Delay, float64_int64s(((float64)TimeReference)*1000/SamplesPerSec));
1257 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Delay_Source, "Container (bext)");
1258 }
1259
1260 //Specific cases
1261 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_DTS_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_SMPTEST0337_YES)
1262 if (FormatTag==0x1 && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Wave")) //Some DTS or SMPTE ST 337 streams are coded "1"
1263 {
1264 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_DTS_YES)
1265 {
1266 File_Dts* Parser=new File_Dts;
1267 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid=2;
1268 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1269 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1270 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Wave"))
1271 {
1272 Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
1273 Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
1274 Demux_Level=4; //Intermediate
1275 }
1276 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1277 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1278 }
1279 #endif
1280
1281 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_SMPTEST0337_YES)
1282 {
1283 File_SmpteSt0337* Parser=new File_SmpteSt0337;
1284 Parser->Container_Bits=(int8u)BitsPerSample;
1285 Parser->Aligned=true;
1286 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1287 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1288 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Wave"))
1289 {
1290 Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
1291 Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
1292 Demux_Level=4; //Intermediate
1293 }
1294 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1295 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1296 }
1297 #endif
1298 }
1299 #endif
1300
1301 //Creating the parser
1302 if (0);
1303 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGA_YES)
1304 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("MPEG Audio"))
1305 {
1306 File_Mpega* Parser=new File_Mpega;
1307 Parser->CalculateDelay=true;
1308 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1309 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1310 }
1311 #endif
1312 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AC3_YES)
1313 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("AC-3"))
1314 {
1315 File_Ac3* Parser=new File_Ac3;
1316 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid=2;
1317 Parser->CalculateDelay=true;
1318 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1319 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1320 }
1321 #endif
1322 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_DTS_YES)
1323 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("DTS"))
1324 {
1325 File_Dts* Parser=new File_Dts;
1326 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid=2;
1327 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1328 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1329 }
1330 #endif
1331 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_AAC_YES)
1332 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("AAC"))
1333 {
1334 File_Aac* Parser=new File_Aac;
1335 Parser->Mode=File_Aac::Mode_ADTS;
1336 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid=1;
1337 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1338 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1339 }
1340 #endif
1341 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PCM_YES)
1342 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("PCM"))
1343 {
1344 File_Pcm* Parser=new File_Pcm;
1345 Parser->Codec=Codec;
1346 Parser->Endianness='L';
1347 Parser->BitDepth=(int8u)BitsPerSample;
1348 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1349 if (Demux_Rate)
1350 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid = float64_int64s(Demux_Rate);
1351 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Wave"))
1352 {
1353 Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
1354 Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
1355 Demux_Level=4; //Intermediate
1356 }
1357 #else //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1358 Parser->Frame_Count_Valid=(int64u)-1; //Disabling it, waiting for SMPTE ST 337 parser reject
1359 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1360 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1361 Stream[Stream_ID].IsPcm=true;
1362 }
1363 #endif
1364 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_ADPCM_YES)
1365 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("ADPCM"))
1366 {
1367 //Creating the parser
1368 File_Adpcm MI;
1369 MI.Codec=Codec;
1370
1371 //Parsing
1372 Open_Buffer_Init(&MI);
1373 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI, 0);
1374
1375 //Filling
1376 Finish(&MI);
1377 Merge(MI, StreamKind_Last, 0, StreamPos_Last);
1378 }
1379 #endif
1380 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_OGG_YES)
1381 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("Vorbis")
1382 && FormatTag!=0x566F) //0x566F has config in this chunk
1383 {
1384 File_Ogg* Parser=new File_Ogg;
1385 Parser->ShouldContinueParsing=true;
1386 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1387 }
1388 #endif
1389 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1390 Open_Buffer_Init(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]);
1391
1392 //Options
1393 if (Element_Offset+2>Element_Size)
1394 return; //No options
1395
1396 //Parsing
1397 int16u Option_Size;
1398 Get_L2 (Option_Size, "cbSize");
1399
1400 //Filling
1401 if (Option_Size>0)
1402 {
1403 if (0);
1404 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Codec)==__T("MPEG Audio"))
1405 {
1406 if (Option_Size==12)
1407 AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_Mpega();
1408 else
1409 Skip_XX(Option_Size, "MPEG Audio - Uknown");
1410 }
1411 else if (Codec==__T("AAC") || Codec==__T("FF") || Codec==__T("8180"))
1412 AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_Aac();
1413 else if (FormatTag==0x566F) //Vorbis with Config in this chunk
1414 AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_Vorbis();
1415 else if (FormatTag==0x6750) //Vorbis with Config in this chunk
1416 AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_Vorbis2();
1417 else if (FormatTag==0xFFFE) //Extensible Wave
1418 AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_ExtensibleWave();
1419 else if (Element_Offset+Option_Size<=Element_Size)
1420 Skip_XX(Option_Size, "Unknown");
1421 else if (Element_Offset!=Element_Size)
1422 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Error");
1423 }
1424}

1458//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1459void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_Vorbis()
1460{
1461 //Parsing
1462 Element_Begin1("Vorbis options");
1463 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_OGG_YES)
1464 File_Ogg_SubElement MI;
1465 Open_Buffer_Init(&MI);
1466 Element_Begin1("Element sizes");
1467 //All elements parsing, except last one
1468 std::vector<size_t> Elements_Size;
1469 size_t Elements_TotalSize=0;
1470 int8u Elements_Count;
1471 Get_L1(Elements_Count, "Element count");
1472 Elements_Size.resize(Elements_Count+1); //+1 for the last block
1473 for (int8u Pos=0; Pos<Elements_Count; Pos++)
1474 {
1475 int8u Size;
1476 Get_L1(Size, "Size");
1477 Elements_Size[Pos]=Size;
1478 Elements_TotalSize+=Size;
1479 }
1480 Element_End0();
1481 if (Element_Offset+Elements_TotalSize>Element_Size)
1482 return;
1483 //Adding the last block
1484 Elements_Size[Elements_Count]=(size_t)(Element_Size-(Element_Offset+Elements_TotalSize));
1485 Elements_Count++;
1486 //Parsing blocks
1487 for (int8u Pos=0; Pos<Elements_Count; Pos++)
1488 {
1489 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI, Elements_Size[Pos]);
1490 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI, 0);
1491 Element_Offset+=Elements_Size[Pos];
1492 }
1493 //Finalizing
1494 Finish(&MI);
1495 Merge(MI, StreamKind_Last, 0, StreamPos_Last);
1496 Clear(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_BitDepth); //Resolution is not valid for Vorbis
1497 Element_Show();
1498 #else //MEDIAINFO_MPEG4_YES
1499 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "(Vorbis headers)");
1500 #endif
1501 Element_End0();
1502}

1522//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1523void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_auds_ExtensibleWave()
1524{
1525 //Parsing
1526 int128u SubFormat;
1527 int32u ChannelMask;
1528 Skip_L2( "ValidBitsPerSample / SamplesPerBlock");
1529 Get_L4 (ChannelMask, "ChannelMask");
1530 Get_GUID(SubFormat, "SubFormat");
1531
1532 FILLING_BEGIN();
1533 if ((SubFormat.hi&0xFFFFFFFFFFFF0000LL)==0x0010000000000000LL && SubFormat.lo==0x800000AA00389B71LL)
1534 {
1535 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16), Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
1536 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_CodecID, Ztring().From_GUID(SubFormat), true);
1537 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, MediaInfoLib::Config.Codec_Get(Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16)), true);
1538
1539 //Creating the parser
1540 if (0);
1541 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PCM_YES)
1542 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Audio, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_Number((int16u)SubFormat.hi, 16))==__T("PCM"))
1543 {
1544 //Creating the parser
1545 File_Pcm* Parser=new File_Pcm;
1546 Parser->Codec=Ztring().From_GUID(SubFormat);
1547 Parser->Endianness='L';
1548 Parser->Sign='S';
1549 Parser->BitDepth=(int8u)BitsPerSample;
1550 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1551 if (Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Format)==__T("Wave"))
1552 {
1553 Parser->Demux_Level=2; //Container
1554 Parser->Demux_UnpacketizeContainer=true;
1555 Demux_Level=4; //Intermediate
1556 }
1557 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1558 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1559 Stream[Stream_ID].IsPcm=true;
1560 }
1561 #endif
1562
1563 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1564 Open_Buffer_Init(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]);
1565 }
1566 else
1567 {
1568 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_GUID(SubFormat), Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
1569 }
1570 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelPositions, ExtensibleWave_ChannelMask(ChannelMask));
1571 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_ChannelPositions_String2, ExtensibleWave_ChannelMask2(ChannelMask));
1572 FILLING_END();
1573}

1575//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1576void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_iavs()
1577{
1578 //Standard video header before Iavs?
1579 if (Element_Size==72)
1580 {
1581 Element_Begin0();
1582 AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_vids();
1583 Element_End0();
1584 }
1585
1586 Element_Info1("Interleaved Audio/Video");
1587
1588 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_DVDIF_YES
1589 if (Element_Size<8*4)
1590 return;
1591
1592 //Parsing
1593 DV_FromHeader=new File_DvDif();
1594 Open_Buffer_Init(DV_FromHeader);
1595
1596 //DVAAuxSrc
1597 ((File_DvDif*)DV_FromHeader)->AuxToAnalyze=0x50; //Audio source
1598 Open_Buffer_Continue(DV_FromHeader, 4);
1599 //DVAAuxCtl
1600 ((File_DvDif*)DV_FromHeader)->AuxToAnalyze=0x51; //Audio control
1601 Open_Buffer_Continue(DV_FromHeader, Buffer+Buffer_Offset+(size_t)Element_Offset, 4);
1602 Element_Offset+=4;
1603 //DVAAuxSrc1
1604 Skip_L4( "DVAAuxSrc1");
1605 //DVAAuxCtl1
1606 Skip_L4( "DVAAuxCtl1");
1607 //DVVAuxSrc
1608 ((File_DvDif*)DV_FromHeader)->AuxToAnalyze=0x60; //Video source
1609 Open_Buffer_Continue(DV_FromHeader, 4);
1610 //DVAAuxCtl
1611 ((File_DvDif*)DV_FromHeader)->AuxToAnalyze=0x61; //Video control
1612 Open_Buffer_Continue(DV_FromHeader, 4);
1613 //Reserved
1614 if (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
1615 {
1616 Skip_L4( "DVReserved");
1617 Skip_L4( "DVReserved");
1618 }
1619
1620 Finish(DV_FromHeader);
1621
1622 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Video);
1623 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(new File_DvDif);
1624 Open_Buffer_Init(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[0]);
1625
1626 #else //MEDIAINFO_DVDIF_YES
1627 //Parsing
1628 Skip_L4( "DVAAuxSrc");
1629 Skip_L4( "DVAAuxCtl");
1630 Skip_L4( "DVAAuxSrc1");
1631 Skip_L4( "DVAAuxCtl1");
1632 Skip_L4( "DVVAuxSrc");
1633 Skip_L4( "DVVAuxCtl");
1634 Skip_L4( "DVReserved");
1635 Skip_L4( "DVReserved");
1636
1637 //Filling
1638 Ztring Codec; Codec.From_CC4(Stream[Stream_ID].fccHandler);
1639 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Video);
1640 float32 FrameRate=Retrieve(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_FrameRate).To_float32();
1641 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Codec, Codec); //May be replaced by codec parser
1642 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Codec_CC, Codec);
1643 if (Codec==__T("dvsd")
1644 || Codec==__T("dvsl"))
1645 {
1646 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width, 720);
1647 if (FrameRate==25.000) Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height, 576);
1648 else if (FrameRate==29.970) Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height, 480);
1649 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_DisplayAspectRatio, 4.0/3, 3, true);
1650 }
1651 else if (Codec==__T("dvhd"))
1652 {
1653 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Width, 1440);
1654 if (FrameRate==25.000) Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height, 1152);
1655 else if (FrameRate==30.000) Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_Height, 960);
1656 Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, Video_DisplayAspectRatio, 4.0/3, 3, true);
1657 }
1658 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Audio);
1659 CodecID_Fill(Codec, Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
1660 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec, Codec); //May be replaced by codec parser
1661 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Codec_CC, Codec);
1662 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DVDIF_YES
1663}

1676//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1677void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_txts()
1678{
1679 Element_Info1("Text");
1680
1681 //Parsing
1682 Ztring Format;
1683 if (Element_Size)
1684 {
1685 Get_Local(10, Format, "Format");
1686 Skip_XX(22, "Unknown");
1687 }
1688
1689 FILLING_BEGIN_PRECISE();
1690 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
1691
1692 if (Element_Size==0)
1693 {
1694 //Creating the parser
1695 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_SUBRIP_YES)
1696 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(new File_SubRip);
1697 #endif
1698 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_OTHERTEXT_YES)

1700 #endif
1701
1702 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1703 Open_Buffer_Init(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]);
1704 }
1705 else
1706 {
1707 Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, Text_Format, Format);
1708 }
1709 FILLING_END();
1710}
1711
1712//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1713void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strf_vids()
1714{
1715 Element_Info1("Video");
1716
1717 //Parsing
1718 int32u Compression, Width, Height;
1719 int16u Resolution;
1720 Skip_L4( "Size");
1721 Get_L4 (Width, "Width");
1722 Get_L4 (Height, "Height");
1723 Skip_L2( "Planes");
1724 Get_L2 (Resolution, "BitCount"); //Do not use it
1725 Get_C4 (Compression, "Compression");
1726 Skip_L4( "SizeImage");
1727 Skip_L4( "XPelsPerMeter");
1728 Skip_L4( "YPelsPerMeter");
1729 Skip_L4( "ClrUsed");
1730 Skip_L4( "ClrImportant");
1731
1732 //Filling
1733 Stream[Stream_ID].Compression=Compression;
1734
1735 if (Compression==CC4("DXSB"))
1736 {
1737 //Divx.com hack for subtitle, this is a text stream in a DivX Format
1738 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "DivX", Unlimited, true, true);
1739 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
1740 }
1741 else
1742 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Video);
1743
1744 //Filling
1745 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff);
1746 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Codec), Ztring().From_CC4(Compression).To_Local().c_str()); //FormatTag, may be replaced by codec parser
1747 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Codec_CC), Ztring().From_CC4(Compression).To_Local().c_str()); //FormatTag
1748 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Width", Width, 10, true);
1749 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Height", Height>=0x80000000?(-((int32s)Height)):Height, 10, true); // AVI can use negative height for raw to signal that it's coded top-down, not bottom-up
1750 if (Resolution==32 && Compression==0x74736363) //tscc
1751 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", 8);
1752 else if (Compression==0x44495633) //DIV3
1753 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", 8);
1754 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression)).find(__T("Canopus"))!=std::string::npos) //Canopus codecs
1755 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/3);
1756 else if (Compression==0x44585342) //DXSB
1757 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution);
1758 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_ColorSpace).find(__T("RGBA"))!=std::string::npos) //RGB codecs
1759 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/4);
1760 else if (Compression==0x00000000 //RGB
1761 || MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_ColorSpace).find(__T("RGB"))!=std::string::npos) //RGB codecs
1762 {
1763 if (Resolution==32)
1764 {
1765 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Fill_Parameter(StreamKind_Last, Generic_Format), "RGBA", Unlimited, true, true);
1766 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/4); //With Alpha
1767 }
1768 else
1769 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution<=16?8:(Resolution/3)); //indexed or normal
1770 }
1771 else if (Compression==0x56503632 //VP62
1772 || MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_Format)==__T("H.263") //H.263
1773 || MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(StreamKind_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_Format)==__T("VC-1")) //VC-1
1774 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "BitDepth", Resolution/3);
1775 Stream[Stream_ID].StreamKind=StreamKind_Last;
1776
1777 //Creating the parser
1778 if (0);
1779 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_FFV1_YES)
1780 else if (MediaInfoLib::Config.CodecID_Get(Stream_Video, InfoCodecID_Format_Riff, Ztring().From_CC4(Compression), InfoCodecID_Format)==__T("FFV1"))
1781 {
1782 File_Ffv1* Parser=new File_Ffv1;
1783 Parser->Width=Width;
1784 Parser->Height=Height;
1785 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1786 }
1787 #endif
1788 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_HUFFYUV_YES)

1958//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1959void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_strh()
1960{
1961 Element_Name("Stream header");
1962
1963 //Parsing
1964 int32u fccType, fccHandler, Scale, Rate, Start, Length;
1965 int16u Left, Top, Right, Bottom;
1966 Get_C4 (fccType, "fccType");
1967 switch (fccType)
1968 {
1969 case Elements::AVI__hdlr_strl_strh_auds :
1970 Get_L4 (fccHandler, "fccHandler");
1971 break;
1972 default:
1973 Get_C4 (fccHandler, "fccHandler");
1974 }
1975 Skip_L4( "Flags");
1976 Skip_L2( "Priority");
1977 Skip_L2( "Language");
1978 Skip_L4( "InitialFrames");
1979 Get_L4 (Scale, "Scale");
1980 Get_L4 (Rate, "Rate"); //Rate/Scale is stream tick rate in ticks/sec
1981 Get_L4 (Start, "Start");
1982 Get_L4 (Length, "Length");
1983 Skip_L4( "SuggestedBufferSize");
1984 Skip_L4( "Quality");
1985 Skip_L4( "SampleSize");
1986 Get_L2 (Left, "Frame_Left");
1987 Get_L2 (Top, "Frame_Top");
1988 Get_L2 (Right, "Frame_Right");
1989 Get_L2 (Bottom, "Frame_Bottom");
1990 if(Element_Offset<Element_Size)
1991 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
1992
1993 //Filling
1994 float32 FrameRate=0;
1995 if (Rate>0 && Scale>0)
1996 {
1997 //FrameRate (without known value detection)
1998 FrameRate=((float32)Rate)/Scale;
1999 if (FrameRate>1)
2000 {
2001 float32 Rest=FrameRate-(int32u)FrameRate;
2002 if (Rest<0.01)
2003 FrameRate-=Rest;
2004 else if (Rest>0.99)
2005 FrameRate+=1-Rest;
2006 else
2007 {
2008 float32 Rest1001=FrameRate*1001/1000-(int32u)(FrameRate*1001/1000);
2009 if (Rest1001<0.001)
2010 FrameRate=(float32)((int32u)(FrameRate*1001/1000))*1000/1001;
2011 if (Rest1001>0.999)
2012 FrameRate=(float32)((int32u)(FrameRate*1001/1000)+1)*1000/1001;
2013 }
2014 }
2015
2016 //Duration
2017 if (FrameRate)
2018 {
2019 int64u Duration=float32_int64s((1000*(float32)Length)/FrameRate);
2020 if (avih_TotalFrame>0 //avih_TotalFrame is here because some files have a wrong Audio Duration if TotalFrame==0 (which is a bug, of course!)
2021 && (avih_FrameRate==0 || Duration<((float32)avih_TotalFrame)/avih_FrameRate*1000*1.10) //Some file have a nearly perfect header, except that the value is false, trying to detect it (false if 10% more than 1st video)
2022 && (avih_FrameRate==0 || Duration>((float32)avih_TotalFrame)/avih_FrameRate*1000*0.90)) //Some file have a nearly perfect header, except that the value is false, trying to detect it (false if 10% less than 1st video)
2023 {
2024 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration", Duration);
2025 }
2026 }
2027 }
2028 switch (fccType)
2029 {
2030 case Elements::AVI__hdlr_strl_strh_vids :
2031 if (FrameRate>0) Fill(Stream_Video, StreamPos_Last, "FrameRate", FrameRate, 3);
2032 case Elements::AVI__hdlr_strl_strh_txts :
2033 if (Right-Left>0) Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, "Width", Right-Left, 10, true);
2034 if (Bottom-Top>0) Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, "Height", Bottom-Top, 10, true);
2035 break;
2036 default: ;
2037 }
2038 Stream[Stream_ID].fccType=fccType;
2039 Stream[Stream_ID].fccHandler=fccHandler;
2040 Stream[Stream_ID].Scale=Scale;
2041 Stream[Stream_ID].Rate=Rate;
2042 Stream[Stream_ID].Start=Start;
2043 Stream[Stream_ID].Length=Length;
2044}

2059//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2060void File_Riff::AVI__hdlr_strl_vprp()
2061{
2062 Element_Name("Video properties");
2063
2064 //Parsing
2065 int32u FieldPerFrame;
2066 int16u FrameAspectRatio_H, FrameAspectRatio_W;
2067 Skip_L4( "VideoFormatToken");
2068 Skip_L4( "VideoStandard");
2069 Skip_L4( "VerticalRefreshRate");
2070 Skip_L4( "HTotalInT");
2071 Skip_L4( "VTotalInLines");
2072 Get_L2 (FrameAspectRatio_H, "FrameAspectRatio Height");
2073 Get_L2 (FrameAspectRatio_W, "FrameAspectRatio Width");
2074 Skip_L4( "FrameWidthInPixels");
2075 Skip_L4( "FrameHeightInLines");
2076 Get_L4 (FieldPerFrame, "FieldPerFrame");
2077 vector<int32u> VideoYValidStartLines;
2078 for (int32u Pos=0; Pos<FieldPerFrame; Pos++)
2079 {
2080 Element_Begin1("Field");
2081 int32u VideoYValidStartLine;
2082 Skip_L4( "CompressedBMHeight");
2083 Skip_L4( "CompressedBMWidth");
2084 Skip_L4( "ValidBMHeight");
2085 Skip_L4( "ValidBMWidth");
2086 Skip_L4( "ValidBMXOffset");
2087 Skip_L4( "ValidBMYOffset");
2088 Skip_L4( "VideoXOffsetInT");
2089 Get_L4 (VideoYValidStartLine, "VideoYValidStartLine");
2090 VideoYValidStartLines.push_back(VideoYValidStartLine);
2091 Element_End0();
2092 }
2093 if(Element_Offset<Element_Size)
2094 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
2095
2096 FILLING_BEGIN();
2097 if (FrameAspectRatio_H && FrameAspectRatio_W)
2098 Fill(Stream_Video, 0, Video_DisplayAspectRatio, ((float32)FrameAspectRatio_W)/FrameAspectRatio_H, 3);
2099 switch (FieldPerFrame)
2100 {
2101 case 1 :
2102 Fill(Stream_Video, 0, Video_ScanType, "Progressive");
2103 break;
2104 case 2 :
2105 Fill(Stream_Video, 0, Video_ScanType, "Interlaced");
2106 if (VideoYValidStartLines.size()==2 && VideoYValidStartLines[0]<VideoYValidStartLines[1])
2107 Fill(Stream_Video, 0, Video_ScanOrder, "TFF");
2108 if (VideoYValidStartLines.size()==2 && VideoYValidStartLines[0]>VideoYValidStartLines[1])
2109 Fill(Stream_Video, 0, Video_ScanOrder, "BFF");
2110 default: ;
2111 }
2112 FILLING_END();
2113}

2327 Fill(StreamKind, StreamPos, General_Genre, Value);
2328 if (!ISGN.empty())
2329 Fill(StreamKind, StreamPos, General_Genre, ISGN);
2330 }
2331 break;
2332 default :
2333 if (!Value.empty())
2334 {
2335 if (Parameter!=(size_t)-1)
2336 Fill(StreamKind, StreamPos, Parameter, Value);
2337 else
2338 Fill(StreamKind, StreamPos, Ztring().From_CC4((int32u)Element_Code).To_Local().c_str(), Value, true);
2339 }
2340 }

2343//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2344void File_Riff::AVI__JUNK()
2345{
2346 Element_Name("Garbage"); //Library defined size for padding, often used to store library name
2347
2348 if (Element_Size<8)
2349 {
2350 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Junk");
2351 return;
2352 }
2353
2354 //Detect DivX files
2355 if (CC5(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)==CC5("DivX "))
2356 {
2357 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "DivX", Unlimited, true, true);
2358 }
2359 //MPlayer
2360 else if (CC8(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)==CC8("[= MPlay") && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library).empty())
2361 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library, "MPlayer");
2362 //Scenalyzer
2363 else if (CC8(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)==CC8("scenalyz") && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library).empty())
2364 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library, "Scenalyzer");
2365 //FFMpeg broken files detection
2366 else if (CC8(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)==CC8("odmldmlh"))
2367 dmlh_TotalFrame=0; //this is not normal to have this string in a JUNK block!!! and in files tested, in this case TotalFrame is broken too
2368 //VirtualDubMod
2369 else if (CC8(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)==CC8("INFOISFT"))
2370 {
2371 int32u Size=LittleEndian2int32u(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+8);
2372 if (Size>Element_Size-12)
2373 Size=(int32u)Element_Size-12;
2374 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library, (const char*)(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+12), Size);
2375 }
2376 else if (CC8(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)==CC8("INFOIENG"))
2377 {
2378 int32u Size=LittleEndian2int32u(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+8);
2379 if (Size>Element_Size-12)
2380 Size=(int32u)Element_Size-12;
2381 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library, (const char*)(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+12), Size);
2382 }
2383 //Other libraries?
2384 else if (CC1(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)>=CC1("A") && CC1(Buffer+Buffer_Offset)<=CC1("z") && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library).empty())
2385 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Encoded_Library, (const char*)(Buffer+Buffer_Offset), (size_t)Element_Size);
2386
2387 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Data");
2388}

2390//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2391void File_Riff::AVI__MD5_()
2392{
2393 //Parsing
2394 while (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
2395 {
2396 int128u MD5Stored;
2397 Get_L16 (MD5Stored, "MD5");
2398 Ztring MD5_PerItem;
2399 MD5_PerItem.From_Number(MD5Stored, 16);
2400 while (MD5_PerItem.size()<32)
2401 MD5_PerItem.insert(MD5_PerItem.begin(), '0'); //Padding with 0, this must be a 32-byte string
2402 MD5_PerItem.MakeLowerCase();
2403 MD5s.push_back(MD5_PerItem);
2404 }
2405}

2476{
2477 if (Element_Code==Elements::AVI__JUNK)
2478 {
2479 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Junk");
2480 AVI__movi_StreamJump();
2481 return;
2482 }
2483
2484 if (Element_Code!=(int64u)-1)
2485 Stream_ID=(int32u)(Element_Code&0xFFFF0000);
2486 else
2487 Stream_ID=(int32u)-1;
2488
2489 if (Stream_ID==0x69780000) //ix..
2490 {
2491 //AVI Standard Index Chunk
2492 AVI__hdlr_strl_indx();
2493 Stream_ID=(int32u)(Element_Code&0x0000FFFF)<<16;
2494 AVI__movi_StreamJump();

2496 }
2497 if ((Element_Code&0x0000FFFF)==0x00006978) //..ix (Out of specs, but found in a Adobe After Effects CS4 DV file

2500 AVI__hdlr_strl_indx();
2501 Stream_ID=(int32u)(Element_Code&0xFFFF0000);
2502 AVI__movi_StreamJump();
2503 return;
2504 }
2505
2506 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2507 if (Stream[Stream_ID].Rate) //AVI
2508 {

2510 Element_Code=((Element_Code_Old>>24)&0xF)*10+((Element_Code_Old>>16)&0xF);

2512 FrameInfo.DTS=Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded*1000000000*Stream[Stream_ID].Scale/Stream[Stream_ID].Rate;

2514 Element_Code=Element_Code_Old;
2515 Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded=(int64u)-1;
2516 }
2517 else //WAV
2518 {
2519 //TODO
2520 }
2521 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2522
2523 Stream[Stream_ID].PacketPos++;
2524
2525 //Finished?
2526 if (!Stream[Stream_ID].SearchingPayload)
2527 {
2528 Element_DoNotShow();
2529 AVI__movi_StreamJump();
2530 return;
2531 }
2532
2533 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2534 if (Config_Trace_Level)
2535 {
2536 switch (Element_Code&0x0000FFFF) //2 last bytes
2537 {
2538 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx_____ : Element_Info1("DV"); break;
2539 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___db :
2540 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___dc : Element_Info1("Video"); break;
2541 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___sb :
2542 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___tx : Element_Info1("Text"); break;
2543 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___wb : Element_Info1("Audio"); break;
2544 default : Element_Info1("Unknown"); break;
2545 }
2546 Element_Info1(Stream[Stream_ID].PacketPos);
2547 }
2548 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2549
2550 //Some specific stuff
2551 switch (Element_Code&0x0000FFFF) //2 last bytes
2552 {
2553 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___tx : AVI__movi_xxxx___tx(); break;
2554 default : ;
2555 }
2556
2557 //Parsing
2558 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
2559 if (Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos])
2560 {
2561 if (FrameInfo.PTS!=(int64u)-1)
2562 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]->FrameInfo.PTS=FrameInfo.PTS;
2563 if (FrameInfo.DTS!=(int64u)-1)
2564 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]->FrameInfo.DTS=FrameInfo.DTS;
2565
2566 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos], Buffer+Buffer_Offset+(size_t)Element_Offset, (size_t)(Element_Size-Element_Offset));
2567 Element_Show();
2568 if (Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size()==1 && Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]->Buffer_Size>0)
2569 Stream[Stream_ID].ChunksAreComplete=false;
2570
2571 if (Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size()>1)
2572 {
2573 if (!Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsAccepted] && Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsFinished])
2574 {
2575 delete *(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.begin()+Pos);
2576 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.erase(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.begin()+Pos);
2577 Pos--;
2578 }
2579 else if (Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size()>1 && Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsAccepted])
2580 {
2581 File__Analyze* Parser=Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos];
2582 for (size_t Pos2=0; Pos2<Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.size(); Pos2++)
2583 {
2584 if (Pos2!=Pos)
2585 delete *(Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.begin()+Pos2);
2586 }
2587 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.clear();
2588 Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
2589 Pos=0;
2590 }
2591 }
2592
2593 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2594 if (Config->Demux_EventWasSent)
2595 {
2596 Demux_Parser=Stream[Stream_ID].Parsers[Pos];
2597 return;
2598 }
2599 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
2600 }
2601 Element_Offset=Element_Size;
2602
2603 //Some specific stuff
2604 switch (Element_Code&0x0000FFFF) //2 last bytes
2605 {
2606 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx_____ :
2607 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___db :
2608 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___dc : AVI__movi_xxxx___dc(); break;
2609 case Elements::AVI__movi_xxxx___wb : AVI__movi_xxxx___wb(); break;
2610 default : ;
2611 }
2612
2613 //We must always parse moov?
2614 AVI__movi_StreamJump();
2615
2616 Element_Show();
2617}

2674//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2675void File_Riff::AVI__movi_StreamJump()
2676{
2677 //Jump to next useful data
2678 if (!Index_Pos.empty())
2679 {
2680 if (Index_Pos.begin()->first<=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset && Element_Code!=Elements::AVI__movi)
2681 Index_Pos.erase(Index_Pos.begin());
2682 int64u ToJump=File_Size;
2683 if (!Index_Pos.empty())
2684 ToJump=Index_Pos.begin()->first;
2685 if (ToJump>File_Size)
2686 ToJump=File_Size;
2687 if (ToJump>=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2)) //We want always Element movi
2688 {
2689 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2690 if (Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong() && SecondPass)
2691 Hash_ParseUpTo=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2);
2692 else
2693 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2694 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2), "AVI"); //Not in this chunk
2695 }
2696 else if (ToJump!=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+(Element_Code==Elements::AVI__movi?0:Element_Size))
2697 {
2698 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2699 if (Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong() && SecondPass)
2700 Hash_ParseUpTo=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2);
2701 else
2702 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2703 GoTo(ToJump, "AVI"); //Not just after
2704 }
2705 }
2706 else if (stream_Count==0)
2707 {
2708 //Jumping
2709 Element_Show();
2710 if (rec__Present)
2711 Element_End0();
2712 Info("movi, Jumping to end of chunk");
2713 if (SecondPass)
2714 {
2715 std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator Temp=Stream.begin();
2716 while (Temp!=Stream.end())
2717 {
2718 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Temp->second.Parsers.size(); ++Pos)
2719 {
2720 Temp->second.Parsers[Pos]->Fill();
2721 Temp->second.Parsers[Pos]->Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
2722 }
2723 ++Temp;
2724 }
2725 Finish("AVI"); //The rest is already parsed
2726 }
2727 else
2728 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(), "AVI");
2729 }
2730 else if (Stream_Structure_Temp!=Stream_Structure.end())
2731 {
2732 do
2733 Stream_Structure_Temp++;
2734 while (Stream_Structure_Temp!=Stream_Structure.end() && !(Stream[(int32u)Stream_Structure_Temp->second.Name].SearchingPayload && Config->ParseSpeed<1.0));
2735 if (Stream_Structure_Temp!=Stream_Structure.end())
2736 {
2737 int64u ToJump=Stream_Structure_Temp->first;
2738 if (ToJump>=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2))
2739 {
2740 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2741 if (Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong() && SecondPass)
2742 Hash_ParseUpTo=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2);
2743 else
2744 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2745 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get(Element_Level-2), "AVI"); //Not in this chunk
2746 }
2747 else if (ToJump!=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Size)
2748 {
2749 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2750 if (Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong() && SecondPass)
2751 Hash_ParseUpTo=ToJump;
2752 else
2753 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2754 GoTo(ToJump, "AVI"); //Not just after
2755 }
2756 }
2757 else
2758 Finish("AVI");
2759 }
2760}

2941//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2942void File_Riff::CDDA_fmt_()
2943{
2944 //Specs: http://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compact_Disc_Audio_track
2945 //Specs: http://www.moon-soft.com/program/FORMAT/sound/cda.htm
2946
2947 Element_Name("Stream format");
2948
2949 //Parsing
2950 int32u id;
2951 int16u Version, tracknb=1;
2952 int8u TPositionF=0, TPositionS=0, TPositionM=0, TDurationF=0, TDurationS=0, TDurationM=0;
2953 Get_L2 (Version, "Version"); // Always 1
2954 if (Version!=1)
2955 {
2956 //Not supported
2957 Skip_XX(Element_Size-2, "Data");
2958 return;
2959 }
2960 Get_L2 (tracknb, "Number"); // Start at 1
2961 Get_L4 (id, "id");
2962 Skip_L4( "offset"); // in frames //Priority of FSM format
2963 Skip_L4( "Duration"); // in frames //Priority of FSM format
2964 Get_L1 (TPositionF, "Track_PositionF"); // in frames
2965 Get_L1 (TPositionS, "Track_PositionS"); // in seconds
2966 Get_L1 (TPositionM, "Track_PositionM"); // in minutes
2967 Skip_L1( "empty");
2968 Get_L1 (TDurationF, "Track_DurationF"); // in frames
2969 Get_L1 (TDurationS, "Track_DurationS"); // in seconds
2970 Get_L1 (TDurationM, "Track_DurationM"); // in minutes
2971 Skip_L1( "empty");
2972
2973 FILLING_BEGIN();
2974 int32u TPosition=TPositionM*60*75+TPositionS*75+TPositionF;
2975 int32u TDuration=TDurationM*60*75+TDurationS*75+TDurationF;
2976
2977 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Track_Position, tracknb);
2978 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "CDDA");

3181//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3182void File_Riff::QLCM_fmt_()
3183{
3184 //Parsing
3185 Ztring codec_name;
3186 int128u codec_guid;
3187 int32u num_rates;
3188 int16u codec_version, average_bps, packet_size, block_size, sampling_rate, sample_size;
3189 int8u major, minor;
3190 Get_L1 (major, "major");
3191 Get_L1 (minor, "minor");
3192 Get_GUID(codec_guid, "codec-guid");
3193 Get_L2 (codec_version, "codec-version");
3194 Get_Local(80, codec_name, "codec-name");
3195 Get_L2 (average_bps, "average-bps");
3196 Get_L2 (packet_size, "packet-size");
3197 Get_L2 (block_size, "block-size");
3198 Get_L2 (sampling_rate, "sampling-rate");
3199 Get_L2 (sample_size, "sample-size");
3200 Element_Begin1("rate-map-table");
3201 Get_L4 (num_rates, "num-rates");
3202 for (int32u rate=0; rate<num_rates; rate++)
3203 {
3204 Skip_L2( "rate-size");
3205 Skip_L2( "rate-octet");
3206 }
3207 Element_End0();
3208 Skip_L4( "Reserved");
3209 Skip_L4( "Reserved");
3210 Skip_L4( "Reserved");
3211 Skip_L4( "Reserved");
3212 if (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
3213 Skip_L4( "Reserved"); //Some files don't have the 5th reserved dword
3214
3215 FILLING_BEGIN_PRECISE();
3216 Stream_Prepare (Stream_Audio);
3217 switch (codec_guid.hi)
3218 {
3219 case Elements::QLCM_QCELP1 :
3220 case Elements::QLCM_QCELP2 : Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Format, "QCELP"); Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Codec, "QCELP"); break;
3221 case Elements::QLCM_EVRC : Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Format, "EVRC"); Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Codec, "EVRC"); break;
3222 case Elements::QLCM_SMV : Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Format, "SMV"); Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Codec, "SMV"); break;
3223 default : ;
3224 }
3225 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitRate, average_bps);
3226 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_SamplingRate, sampling_rate);
3227 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitDepth, sample_size);
3228 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Channel_s_, 1);

3597//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3598void File_Riff::WAVE_data()
3599{
3600 Element_Name("Raw datas");
3601
3602 if (Buffer_DataToParse_End-Buffer_DataToParse_Begin<100)
3603 {
3604 Skip_XX(Buffer_DataToParse_End-Buffer_Offset, "Unknown");
3605 return; //This is maybe embeded in another container, and there is only the header (What is the junk?)
3606 }
3607
3608 FILLING_BEGIN();
3609 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_StreamSize, Buffer_DataToParse_End-Buffer_DataToParse_Begin);
3610 FILLING_END();
3611
3612 //Parsing
3613 Element_Code=(int64u)-1;
3614
3615 FILLING_BEGIN();
3616 int64u Duration=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Duration).To_int64u();
3617 int64u BitRate=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitRate).To_int64u();
3618 if (Duration)
3619 {
3620 int64u BitRate_New=(Buffer_DataToParse_End-Buffer_DataToParse_Begin)*8*1000/Duration;
3621 if (BitRate_New<BitRate*0.95 || BitRate_New>BitRate*1.05)
3622 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitRate, BitRate_New, 10, true); //Correcting the bitrate, it was false in the header
3623 }
3624 else if (BitRate)
3625 {
3626 if (IsSub)
3627 //Retrieving "data" real size, in case of truncated files and/or wave header in another container
3628 Duration=((int64u)LittleEndian2int32u(Buffer+Buffer_Offset-4))*8*1000/BitRate; //TODO: RF64 is not handled
3629 else
3630 Duration=(Buffer_DataToParse_End-Buffer_DataToParse_Begin)*8*1000/BitRate;
3631 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Duration, Duration, 10, true);
3632 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Duration, Duration, 10, true);
3633 }
3634 FILLING_END();
3635}

3642 if (AvgBytesPerSec && Demux_Rate)
3643 {
3644 FrameInfo.DTS=float64_int64s((File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Buffer_DataToParse_Begin)*1000000000.0/AvgBytesPerSec);
3645 FrameInfo.PTS=FrameInfo.DTS;
3646 Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded=float64_int64s(((float64)FrameInfo.DTS)/1000000000.0*Demux_Rate);
3647 }
3648 Demux_random_access=true;
3649 Demux(Buffer+Buffer_Offset, (size_t)Element_Size, ContentType_MainStream);
3650 Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded=(int64u)-1;
3651 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
3652
3653 Element_Code=(int64u)-1;
3654 AVI__movi_xxxx();
3655}

3673void File_Riff::WAVE_fact()
3674{
3675 Element_Name("Sample count");
3676
3677 //Parsing
3678 int64u SamplesCount64;
3679 int32u SamplesCount;
3680 Get_L4 (SamplesCount, "SamplesCount");
3681 SamplesCount64=SamplesCount;
3682 if (SamplesCount64==0xFFFFFFFF)
3683 SamplesCount64=WAVE_fact_samplesCount;
3684
3685 FILLING_BEGIN();
3686 int32u SamplingRate=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_SamplingRate).To_int32u();
3687 if (SamplingRate)
3688 {
3689 //Calculating
3690 int64u Duration=(SamplesCount64*1000)/SamplingRate;
3691
3692 //Coherency test
3693 bool IsOK=true;
3694 if (File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
3695 {
3696 int64u BitRate=Retrieve(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_BitRate).To_int64u();
3697 if (BitRate)
3698 {
3699 int64u Duration_FromBitRate = File_Size * 8 * 1000 / BitRate;
3700 if (Duration_FromBitRate > Duration*1.10 || Duration_FromBitRate < Duration*0.9)
3701 IsOK = false;
3702 }
3703 }
3704
3705 //Filling
3706 if (IsOK)
3707 Fill(Stream_Audio, 0, Audio_Duration, Duration);
3708 }
3709 FILLING_END();
3710}

3758//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3759void File_Riff::W3DI()
3760{
3761 Element_Name("IDVX tags (Out of specs!)");
3762
3763 //Parsing
3764 int32u Size=(int32u)Element_Size;
3765 Ztring Title, Artist, Album, Unknown, Genre, Comment;
3766 int32u TrackPos;
3767 Get_Local(Size, Title, "Title");
3768 Element_Offset=(int32u)Title.size();
3769 Size-=(int32u)Title.size();
3770 if (Size==0) return;
3771 Skip_L1( "Zero"); Size--; //NULL char
3772 Get_Local(Size, Artist, "Artist");
3773 Element_Offset=(int32u)Title.size()+1+(int32u)Artist.size();
3774 Size-=(int32u)Artist.size();
3775 if (Size==0) return;
3776 Skip_L1( "Zero"); Size--; //NULL char
3777 Get_Local(Size, Album, "Album");
3778 Element_Offset=(int32u)Title.size()+1+(int32u)Artist.size()+1+(int32u)Album.size();
3779 Size-=(int32u)Album.size();
3780 if (Size==0) return;
3781 Skip_L1( "Zero"); Size--; //NULL char
3782 Get_Local(Size, Unknown, "Unknown");
3783 Element_Offset=(int32u)Title.size()+1+(int32u)Artist.size()+1+(int32u)Album.size()+1+(int32u)Unknown.size();
3784 Size-=(int32u)Unknown.size();
3785 if (Size==0) return;
3786 Skip_L1( "Zero"); Size--; //NULL char
3787 Get_Local(Size, Genre, "Genre");
3788 Element_Offset=(int32u)Title.size()+1+(int32u)Artist.size()+1+(int32u)Album.size()+1+(int32u)Unknown.size()+1+(int32u)Genre.size();
3789 Size-=(int32u)Genre.size();
3790 if (Size==0) return;
3791 Skip_L1( "Zero"); Size--; //NULL char
3792 Get_Local(Size, Comment, "Comment");
3793 Element_Offset=(int32u)Title.size()+1+(int32u)Artist.size()+1+(int32u)Album.size()+1+(int32u)Unknown.size()+1+(int32u)Genre.size()+1+(int32u)Comment.size();
3794 Size-=(int32u)Comment.size();
3795 if (Size==0) return;
3796 Skip_L1( "Zero"); Size--; //NULL char
3797 Get_L4 (TrackPos, "Track_Position");
3798 if(Element_Offset+8<Element_Size)
3799 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
3800 Element_Begin1("Footer");
3801 Skip_L4( "Size");
3802 Skip_C4( "Name");
3803 Element_End0();
3804
3805 //Filling
3806 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Track, Title);
3807 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Performer, Artist);
3808 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Album, Album);
3809 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "Unknown", Unknown);
3810 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Genre, Genre);
3811 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Comment, Comment);
3812 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Track_Position, TrackPos);
3813}
